=== Post-JSON Summary Table ===

Immediately after the JSON, send a separate message (not part of the JSON) containing:

| Metric                              | Count        |
|-------------------------------------|--------------|
| Total URLs provided                 | [N]          |
| Valid URLs processed into JSON      | [N]          |
| Duplicate URLs excluded             | [N]          |
| Broken / insufficient URLs excluded | [N]          |
| Unique IDs in JSON                  | [N]          |

Integrity Check:
- Total JSON entries may exceed Total URLs when multi-track programs are present. Document as: 1 URL → N entries (multi-track expansion).
- PASS if: Total URLs provided == Valid URLs processed + Excluded URLs, AND all IDs in the JSON are unique.
- FAIL otherwise — list which entries caused the failure.

